 River levels remain high along the River Severn as a result of heavy rainfall. Flooding of roads and farmland continues. 



We expect flooding to affect low lying land & roads adjacent to the River Severn from Tewkesbury to Gloucester. Locations that may be affected include Apperley, Maisemore, Hempsted, and low-lying land at Quedgeley and Stonebench. Severn Ham, Tewkesbury fills.  



Predicted peaks:- 



Mythe Bridge 4.3m to 4.5m Saturday morning, 24/02/2024; 

Haw Bridge, 5.0m to 5.2m Sunday 25/02/2024; 

Sandhurst, 3.6m to 4.0m Sunday 25/02/2024; 

Gloucester 3.2m to 3.6m Sunday 25/02/2024. 



Further rainfall is expected over the next 48 hours, and we expect river levels to remain high over the next few days. We are closely monitoring the situation. 



Please avoid using low lying footpaths near local watercourses and plan driving routes to avoid low lying roads near rivers, which may be flooded. 



This message will be updated by 9am Saturday, 24/02/2024, or as the situation changes.

 River levels remain high along the River Severn as a result of heavy rainfall. Consequently, flooding of roads and farmland is expected. We expect flooding to affect low lying land and roads adjacent to the river from Shrewsbury to Upper Arley. Locations that may be affected are Coalbrookdale, Ironbridge and Bridgnorth. Floodplain at Leighton starts to fill.
The river peaked at Crew Green at 5.84m early this afternoon, Friday 23/02/24.
Predicted Peaks:-
Montford, 5.2 to 5.3m, this afternoon, Friday 23/02/24;
Welshbridge, 2.7 to 2.9m overnight tonight, Friday 23/02/24;
Buildwas, 4.2 to 4.4m, on Saturday morning, 24/02/24;
and Bridgnorth, 3.3 to 3.6m, on Saturday afternoon 24/02/24;
We expect river levels to remain high over the next few days. We are closely monitoring the situation.
Please avoid using low lying footpaths near local watercourses and avoid contact with flood water.
This message will be updated by 9am on 24/02/24, or as the situation changes.

 River levels are rising at the Saxons Lode river gauge due to heavy rainfall. Consequently, flooding of roads and farmland continues. 



We expect flooding to affect low lying land and roads adjacent the river from Highley to Tewkesbury. Locations affected are Stourport, Holt Fleet, Worcester, Kempsey, Severn Stoke, Upton upon Severn, South Quay, Diglis Parade and Hylton Road towpath. Flooded drains may affect the racecourse and Worcester County cricket ground. New Street gate closed at Upton upon Severn due to flooding and may be impassable. 



Predicted peaks:- 



River levels are forecast to peak this afternoon onwards, Friday 23/02/24, at the following levels:- 


Bewdley 3.4m to 3.6m; 

Worcester 4.7m to 4.9m;  

Diglis 4.45m to 4.6m; 

Kempsey Yacht Club 6.7m to 6.9m; 

Saxons Lode 4.9m to 5.1m. 





Further rainfall is expected over the next 48 hours, and we expect river levels to remain high over the next few days. We are closely monitoring the situation. 



This message will be updated by 10am Saturday, 24/02/2024, or as the situation changes.
